{"word":"κρήνη","slug":"κρήνη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κρήνη</b></el> <p/><i>a well, spring, fountain</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>fons</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>φρέαρ</el> (a tank), <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>: —Poets use it in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> for <i>water</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}